citeinfo.origin: Great Barrier Reef Marine Park Authority
citeinfo.title: Reefs

descript.abstract: Major coral reef structures (as defined by the reef shoal edge) and tidal, drying or emergent reef areas within the Great Barrier Reef World Heritage Area
descript.purpose: To represent reef areas within and adjacent to the GBRWHA

theme.themekt: REQUIRED: Reference to a formally registered thesaurus or a similar authoritative source of theme keywords.

attracc.attraccr: Accuracy for attributes estimated to be better than 95% correct.

dataqual.logic: Drying reef areas are logically consistent (i.e.: are completely contained within) indicative reef boundaries
dataqual.complete: Major reef areas, and major exposed portions are present. Smaller exposed areas and shoals may not be present.

horizpa.horizpar: The features have not been statistically tested with precision survey techniques. Positional accuracy varies considerably and dataset should NOT be used for navigation purposes, however, for general use the coverage can be regarded as having a nominal scale of 1:250,000.
